OL,6,FJersey's Census does not differentiate
OL,7,Fbetween British-Isles-born people in
OL,8,Fthe island so some may not be able to
OL,9,Fvote if they never lived in the UK.
OL,11,FBefore January 2024, British people
OL,12,Fliving overseas could only vote in
OL,13,Felections for up to 15 years after
OL,14,Fthey left the country, which the UK
OL,15,Fgovernment called an "arbitrary limit
OL,16,Fon their voting rights".
