OL,3,CMillions more Brits abroad eligible to
OL,4,Cvote in UK General Election
OL,6,FAnyone over 18, a British citizen, or
OL,7,Fan eligible Irish citizen (if
OL,8,Fregistered to vote in Northern
OL,9,FIreland) can vote in UK parliamentary
OL,10,Felections. This applies even if you
OL,11,Fmove abroad.
OL,13,FWhere will overseas votes be counted?
OL,15,FVotes cast by expats will be counted
OL,16,Fas part of the constituency results
OL,17,Fwhere they were previously registered
OL,18,Fto vote when they lived in the UK.
